{"article_id":"WUqRaLYzQuY7PE0t","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Super Tuesday is the biggest day of the Democratic primary campaign .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Fourteen states will hold nominating contests","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"to pick who","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"they think","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"should square off this fall against President Trump .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"There are 1,357 delegates at stake , about a third of all delegates .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"So far , fewer than 4 % of the delegates have been allocated .","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"People will head to the polls all across the country , from Virginia to California , Tennessee to Texas .","depth":3},{"id":8,"text":"The states and voters are diverse .","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"Almost half have significant black populations ,","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"and Latinos figure to be an important factor in the two states with the biggest delegate hauls , California and Texas .","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"There 's a lot on the line , especially for Sen. Bernie Sanders of Vermont and former Vice President Joe Biden .","depth":4},{"id":12,"text":"Sanders is the front-runner .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"He 's built a strong organization in these states","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"that 's been buoyed by a multimillion-dollar ad campaign .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Biden is lagging","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"but hopes to ride a wave of momentum from his big win in South Carolina on Saturday .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"And then there 's Mike Bloomberg .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"After spending hundreds of millions of dollars ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"Bloomberg will be on the ballot for the first time .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"Does he surprise","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"and emerge as an alternative to Sanders ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"or will he siphon votes from Biden ?","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"And what impact might remaining candidates ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"including Sen. Elizabeth Warren ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"have ?","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"This is the most important state of Super Tuesday","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"because of its size .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"Its 415 delegates is more than the nine Super Tuesday contests with the lowest delegate totals combined .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Latinos are expected to make up about 30 % of the electorate .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"Sanders won Latinos overwhelmingly in Nevada ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"and","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"if he runs up the score with them in California ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"he could build a formidable pledged-delegate lead .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"Sanders is the heavy favorite here ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"despite losing to Hillary Clinton in 2016 .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"He has spent about $ 7 million on ads","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"( of the $ 15.5 million","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"he has spent across Super Tuesday states ) ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"according to data as of Feb. 27 from Advertising Analytics","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"provided to NPR .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Biden has spent zero on California TV ads , and just $ 4,000","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"( yes , that 's thousand )","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"on digital .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"A ray of hope for Biden is also","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"even though early voting started a month ago ,","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"fewer ballots have been returned than in past elections .","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"Bloomberg , in contrast , has spent more than $ 71 million","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"and is currently polling below the 15 % threshold","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"required","depth":15},{"id":51,"text":"to get any delegates in all of these contests .","depth":15},{"id":52,"text":"Warren is teetering around the delegate threshold percentage , too ,","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"with most polls conducted before South Carolina .","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"Does she get above 15 % ?","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"Does she pull from Sanders ?","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"Does Biden gain momentum from South Carolina ?","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"A wild card is black voters .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"There were no exit polls in 2016 ;","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"2008 exit polls showed","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"black voters were only 7 % of the electorate .","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"But the California Democratic Party estimates","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"that African Americans are about 16 % of the party .","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"Do they turn out ?","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"Depending on which estimate winds up being correct","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"could determine","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"if Biden makes a dent in the state .","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"This will also be the first significant measure of Asian Americans in this election .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"They were 8 % of the electorate in 2008 ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"and the California Democratic Party estimates","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"they are 10 % now .","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"Polls close :","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"9 p.m . ET","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"( Most polls close at 8 p.m . ET ,","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"but El Paso is in the Mountain time zone . )","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"Everything 's bigger in Texas ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"including the delegate count .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"OK , it 's not as big as California ,","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"but it 's right up there .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"The race is shaping up to be closer than in California .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Polling shows Sanders up by an average of 9 points over Biden .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"Bloomberg is the only other candidate","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"averaging above the 15 % threshold","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"needed","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"to get delegates ,","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"but whether he makes it is something to watch .","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"Some polls have also shown Warren at or above the threshold .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"This state has not always been friendly to Sanders .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"He lost it to Hillary Clinton by more than 30 points in 2016 .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"A number","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"to watch on Tuesday","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"is 33 % , the percentage of the vote","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"he got the last time around .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"Sanders struggled","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"because Clinton had a fairly strong hold on voters of color ,","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"and Texas is expected to be a majority-minority electorate on Tuesday .","depth":16},{"id":96,"text":"In 2016 , it was 57 % nonwhite ,","depth":17},{"id":97,"text":"including 32 % Latino and 19 % black .","depth":17},{"id":98,"text":"Biden 's disadvantages here are advertising and early voting .","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"He 's spent only about $ 89,000 here","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"compared with more than $ 3.7 million for Sanders .","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"Early voting lasted for 10 days , until Friday , the day before Biden 's boost in South Carolina .","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"More than 1 million Democrats voted early .","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"Black voters are key .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"About a third of the electorate in 2016 was African American .","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"Both groups favor Biden ,","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"but the percentages of both are lower in North Carolina than in South Carolina .","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"That means a narrower race between Biden and Sanders .","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"Polls show Biden slightly ahead of Sanders ,","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"and the only other candidate","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"polling at or near threshold","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"is Bloomberg ,","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"who has spent almost $ 15 million on ads in the state .","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"Warren has n't been over 15 % in the state in almost two months .","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"Virginia , with its 7 p.m . ET poll-closing time , will give an early indication","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"of whether moderate Democrats are coalescing around Biden .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"This is a place","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"Clinton won by almost 30 points over Sanders ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"and Biden has now gotten the endorsements of former Gov . Terry McAuliffe and Sen. Tim Kaine , also a former governor .","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"Unite the Country , a superPAC","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"supporting Biden ,","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"believes","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"Biden is starting to do well not just with black voters","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"but with white women over 40 .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"The Virginia suburbs is the place","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"to prove it .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"Clinton won almost two-thirds of white women ,","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"who were 36 % of the electorate ,","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"in addition to blowing out the margins with black voters .","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"She won 84 % of African Americans ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"and they were about a quarter of the electorate .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"There have n't been many good polls in Virginia .","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"The last best one was a Monmouth poll from Feb. 18 ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"which is a lifetime in a presidential primary race .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"It showed essentially a three-way tie for Sanders","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"( 22 % ) ,","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"Bloomberg","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"( 22 % )","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"and Biden","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"( 18 % ) -","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"and it was conducted before Bloomberg 's first debate in Las Vegas ,","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"which was a spotty performance .","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"This is Warren 's home state ,","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"but Sanders is making a play here in this state","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"where 85 % of Democratic voters in 2016 were white .","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"Sanders is actually leading very narrowly in most polls .","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"with no one else","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"polling above threshold","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"- and with former South Bend , Ind. , Mayor Pete Buttigieg out of the race -","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"Sanders and Warren may split the delegates evenly here .","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"Prior to Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar 's decision","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"to drop out of the race ,","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"she was leading Sanders narrowly in polling from a couple of weeks ago .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"Without her ,","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"Sanders could be a favorite ,","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"with only Warren among the other candidates staying around the threshold .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"Biden 's performance in South Carolina and the string of endorsements","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"he has received ,","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"including from Klobuchar ,","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"remains a wild card in Minnesota .","depth":8},{"id":161,"text":"This is one of the three states","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"where Latinos could make a difference .","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"Colorado switched from a caucus to a primary and no entrance polls in 2016 ,","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"so who will turn out is a bit of a wild card .","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"The state party estimates","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"that Latinos could be as many as 1 in 5 voters .","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"The very limited polling in the swing state","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"that now leans blue","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"shows Sanders with a lead","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"and Warren the only other candidate above threshold .","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"But the poll was taken before South Carolina ,","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"and","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"with Buttigieg out ,","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"it 's possible Biden ekes out some delegates .","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"Remarkably , Bloomberg has spent almost $ 10 million on ads in this state","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"and could get shut out of any delegates .","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"This is the state","depth":15},{"id":178,"text":"where Biden has invested most in ads on Super Tuesday","depth":16},{"id":179,"text":"( even though it 's only $ 157,000","depth":17},{"id":180,"text":"and is less than half of what Sanders has put in ) .","depth":17},{"id":181,"text":"There 's a reason for that -","depth":15},{"id":182,"text":"roughly a third of the state 's Democratic electorate was black in 2016 .","depth":16},{"id":183,"text":"Biden is hoping to run up the score here , especially with wealth venture capitalist Tom Steyer out of the way .","depth":17},{"id":184,"text":"Steyer ,","depth":20},{"id":185,"text":"who was competing for black voters ,","depth":20},{"id":186,"text":"spent $ 600,000 on ads in Tennessee .","depth":19},{"id":187,"text":"Steyer dropped out","depth":19},{"id":188,"text":"after finishing third in South Carolina with just 11 % and no delegates","depth":20},{"id":189,"text":"after spending almost $ 24 million on ads there .","depth":20},{"id":190,"text":"This is the most heavily African American Democratic electorate of Super Tuesday .","depth":15},{"id":191,"text":"More than half of Alabama Democrats in the 2016 primary were black .","depth":15},{"id":192,"text":"Biden hopes to run up the score here","depth":15},{"id":193,"text":"and perhaps deny any other candidate delegates .","depth":15},{"id":194,"text":"This state has the highest share of white voters","depth":18},{"id":195,"text":"without a college degree","depth":18},{"id":196,"text":"of any of the Super Tuesday states .","depth":17},{"id":197,"text":"They accounted for more than a third of Democratic voters in the 2016 primary .","depth":16},{"id":198,"text":"It 's a group","depth":17},{"id":199,"text":"Sanders has done well with during the first four contests this year .","depth":17},{"id":200,"text":"And in 2016 , he won the Oklahoma primary by 18 points over Clinton .","depth":16},{"id":201,"text":"Biden showed improvement with white voters","depth":16},{"id":202,"text":"without a college degree in South Carolina .","depth":16},{"id":203,"text":"He has to hope","depth":17},{"id":204,"text":"to do better with them","depth":17},{"id":205,"text":"and that black voters ,","depth":18},{"id":206,"text":"who accounted for 14 % of the 2016 primary electorate ,","depth":18},{"id":207,"text":"give him an overwhelming margin .","depth":17},{"id":208,"text":"There has been very sparse polling .","depth":15},{"id":209,"text":"The latest ,","depth":18},{"id":210,"text":"conducted about two weeks ago and before the Las Vegas debate ,","depth":18},{"id":211,"text":"showed Biden statistically tied with Bloomberg ,","depth":18},{"id":212,"text":"who has spent a whopping $ 5.3 million in the state .","depth":18},{"id":213,"text":"Sanders was teetering on the threshold line .","depth":17},{"id":214,"text":"Warren was below the threshold line ;","depth":18},{"id":215,"text":"it would be pretty remarkable","depth":19},{"id":216,"text":"if she gets no delegates from the state","depth":20},{"id":217,"text":"where she was born and raised .","depth":20},{"id":218,"text":"Arkansas cuts a similar profile to Oklahoma ,","depth":15},{"id":219,"text":"but it had a higher share of the electorate","depth":17},{"id":220,"text":"that was black in 2016","depth":17},{"id":221,"text":"- 27 % of Arkansas Democrats were black ,","depth":17},{"id":222,"text":"and 34 % were whites","depth":18},{"id":223,"text":"without a college degree .","depth":18},{"id":224,"text":"There was one poll at the beginning of February , again before the Las Vegas debate ,","depth":16},{"id":225,"text":"that showed","depth":17},{"id":226,"text":"Bloomberg and Biden statistically tied with about a fifth of the vote , and Sanders and Buttigieg around the threshold line .","depth":17},{"id":227,"text":"A lot will likely change from that .","depth":15},{"id":228,"text":"The Utah Democratic Party estimates","depth":16},{"id":229,"text":"that Latinos account for 14 % of the party in this very white state .","depth":16},{"id":230,"text":"A poll from last week has Sanders ahead with 28 % , Bloomberg at 19 % , Warren 15 % and Biden below the 15 % threshold for delegates .","depth":16},{"id":231,"text":"The poll was conducted after the Las Vegas debate ,","depth":17},{"id":232,"text":"but Bloomberg showed up in the state the day after that debate .","depth":18},{"id":233,"text":"It was Bloomberg 's second in-person trip there ,","depth":19},{"id":234,"text":"and campaigns will tell you ,","depth":20},{"id":235,"text":"there 's no more valuable thing during a campaign than a candidate 's time .","depth":20},{"id":236,"text":"Maine is the whitest state","depth":15},{"id":237,"text":"to vote on Super Tuesday -","depth":15},{"id":238,"text":"the state party estimates","depth":15},{"id":239,"text":"that 96 % of the party is white .","depth":15},{"id":240,"text":"Sanders , the New Englander , led in a poll","depth":17},{"id":241,"text":"conducted the second week of February","depth":17},{"id":242,"text":"with about a quarter of the vote ,","depth":16},{"id":243,"text":"followed by Buttigieg and Bloomberg .","depth":15},{"id":244,"text":"Where does Buttigieg 's support go","depth":17},{"id":245,"text":"now that he 's out of the race ?","depth":17},{"id":246,"text":"It could very well go to Warren ,","depth":17},{"id":247,"text":"who was competing with him for white voters with college degrees .","depth":17},{"id":248,"text":"Biden was slightly below the threshold ,","depth":16},{"id":249,"text":"making this another state","depth":17},{"id":250,"text":"where Biden could get shut out .","depth":17},{"id":251,"text":"This is Sanders ' home state .","depth":11},{"id":252,"text":"He 's the overwhelming favorite","depth":12},{"id":253,"text":"to pick up all 16 delegates here","depth":13},{"id":254,"text":"as he did in 2016 .","depth":13}],"relations":[{"parent":509,"left":261,"right":508,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":0,"right":260,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":260,"left":258,"right":259,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":1,"right":257,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":2,"right":256,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":259,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":508,"left":264,"right":507,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":264,"left":7,"right":263,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":8,"right":262,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":262,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":507,"left":323,"right":506,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":323,"left":11,"right":322,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":322,"left":277,"right":321,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":277,"left":268,"right":276,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":268,"left":266,"right":267,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":266,"left":12,"right":265,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":17,"right":275,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":275,"left":272,"right":274,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":272,"left":269,"right":271,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":269,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":271,"left":270,"right":22,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":270,"left":20,"right":21,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":273,"right":25,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":273,"left":23,"right":24,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":321,"left":280,"right":320,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":279,"right":29,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":279,"left":278,"right":28,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":278,"left":26,"right":27,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":320,"left":283,"right":319,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":283,"left":30,"right":282,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":282,"left":31,"right":281,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":281,"left":32,"right":33,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":319,"left":292,"right":318,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":292,"left":284,"right":291,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":284,"left":34,"right":35,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":291,"left":288,"right":290,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":288,"left":286,"right":287,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":286,"left":36,"right":285,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":37,"right":38,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":287,"left":39,"right":40,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":290,"left":289,"right":43,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":289,"left":41,"right":42,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":318,"left":304,"right":317,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":304,"left":295,"right":303,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":295,"left":44,"right":294,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":294,"left":45,"right":293,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":293,"left":46,"right":47,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":303,"left":300,"right":302,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":300,"left":298,"right":299,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":298,"left":48,"right":297,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":49,"right":296,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":50,"right":51,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":52,"right":53,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":54,"right":301,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":301,"left":55,"right":56,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":317,"left":313,"right":316,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":57,"right":312,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":312,"left":308,"right":311,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":308,"left":58,"right":307,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":307,"left":305,"right":306,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":305,"left":59,"right":60,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":306,"left":61,"right":62,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":311,"left":63,"right":310,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":310,"left":64,"right":309,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":309,"left":65,"right":66,"relation":"attrib